('HP:0004362', 'Abnormality of enteric ganglion morphology', 'An abnormality of the enteric nervous system, which comprises two types of ganglia, the myenteric (Auerbach`s) and submucosal (Meissner`s) plexuses. The enteric nervous system functions to control gut movement, fluid exchange between the gut and its lumen, and local blood flow.'),
