('HP:0011374', 'Incomplete partition of the cochlea type I', 'Incomplete partition I is also known as cystic cochleovestibular malformation, where the cochlea has no bony modiolus, resulting in an empty cystic cochlea. This is accompanied by a dilated cystic vestibule with developmental arrest at the fifth week of gestation.'),
('HP:0011375', 'Cochlear aplasia', 'Absence of the cochlea, a spiral shaped cavity in the inner ear, owing to a developmental defect.'),
