('HP:0011412', 'Ventouse delivery', 'Delivery of newborn by means of a ventouse, a vacuum device used to assist the delivery of a baby when the second stage of labour has not progressed adequately.'),
('HP:0011413', 'Shoulder dystocia', 'Shoulder dystocia occurs when the fetal anterior shoulder impacts against the maternal symphysis following delivery of the vertex.'),
('HP:0011414', 'Hydropic placenta', 'An abnormality of the placenta in which there are numerous cystic spaces within the placenta as well as placental enlargement.'),
