('HP:0012557', 'EEG with centrotemporal focal spike waves', 'EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the centrotemporal region of the brain (also known as the central sulcus), i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.'),
('HP:0012558', 'Abnormal T3/T4 ratio', 'A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that deviates from normal.'),
